wikipedia_page.main: Sir John Salusbury Salusbury-Trelawny, 9th Baronet (2 June 1816 – 4 August 1885), was a British Liberal politician.

link_mentions.page: Records of members of parliament of the United Kingdom

response: Works of art in the town hall include a series of portraits by Lady Laura Russell, the wife of Lord Arthur Russell; the subjects of these portraits include the 4th, 6th and 7th Dukes of Bedford, the local members of parliament, John Pym, Sir John Salusbury-Trelawny, George Byng and  Hugh Luttrell, and the naval and military commanders, Sir Francis Drake and Colonel John Russell.
